<strong></strong>Evening  groups are offered at Badger Creek for  community groups,  wards, family  reunions, etc. These groups will spend  an evening at  Badger Creek  doing workshops of their choice, with the  option of having  dinner  together also. <strong>NOTE:</strong> Not all  workshops are  included in  the evening program. A representative from  Badger Creek will  talk with  the leaders/family representative before  arrival and decide  on what  workshops will run.
<h4><strong>What does Badger Creek provide for evening groups?</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>Workshops (the number depends on group size)</li>
<li>Dinner </li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>When are evening groups scheduled at Badger Creek?</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>Evening  groups are held on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, or Thursday   nights  (beginning June 13 and ending August 12) from 5 p.m. to 9:30  p.m. </li>
</ul>
<h4><strong><strong>What is the cost of an evening group?</strong> </strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>$14 per person (includes dinner and two workshops) </li>
<li>Groups must have at least 12 participants. Groups smaller than 12 participants will need to pay for 12 participants. </li>
</ul>
<p>A  $35 non-refundable deposit is required at the time of registration.  This deposit will be subtracted from the total cost you owe.</p>
<h4><strong>Registration Information</strong></h4>
<p>Registration for the evening groups is on a first-come, first-serve basis. Please call (208) 456-2531 to register your group.</p>
